Narrative

On 7/20/23, the Maryland State Police Computer Crimes Section /Maryland Internet Crimes Against Children Task Force received NCMEC CyberTip # 167022069. The Cyber Tip, generated by Instagram, indicated that a subject uploaded child pornography to the internet. The CyberTip was assigned to Senior Trooper Theodore Cooke #6272 for investigation.

The CyberTip contained 1 reported child pornography file. S/T Cooke reviewed the reported child pornography file and determined that it constitutes child pornography as it is defined under Maryland law. The file is described below:

 

Filename: DpReP2OtRCQc5mXc361118650_6541961859193345_3551376838251141490_n.mp4

Description: 29 second video file showing a black male and female laying on a bed. The male is vaginally penetrating the female with his penis. Both subjects are reasonably believed to be between 12 - 14 years of age based on their physical development and slight presence of pubic hair.

The CyberTip indicated that the following IP address 71.178.218.74 (07-21-2023 02:39:05 UTC) was utilized to upload the reported contraband file.
 

S/T Cooke conducted a query of the upload IP address through an open-source database and determined that it is registered through Verizon Fios and geo-locates generally to the Bowie area of Prince George's County, Maryland.


The suspect identifiers deconflicted with two past cybertip reports which did not contain child pornography. They are listed as follows:
2023-00088026 ( 2/28/23)
2023-00309157 ( 6/26/23)


Based upon the chat messages sent between the sender and recipient included within the Cybertip, it is inferred that the file was sent for comedic/shock value.

This Cybertip is administratively documented and closed pending additional information.
